cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the analysis of images from social networks, specifically Facebook profile images, to estimate the perceived and measured intelligence of users. This involves the use of computer vision techniques to extract image features and machine learning algorithms to predict intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper also touches upon social implications and privacy concerns, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The use of machine learning algorithms to predict intelligence could also fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
